.TH "fsl_dma_hw_free" 9 "fsl_dma_hw_free" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_dma_hw_free \- release resources allocated in fsl_dma_hw_params()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_dma_hw_free
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "substream" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Release the resources allocated in \fBfsl_dma_hw_params\fP and de-program the
registers.

This function can be called multiple times.
